<subSubSection id="1D6E24A9ACB8A6EC823C79251D253991" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FC2D876B6CD6CAD1C02689EA088E0A13" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="27290E992B0668F4D9A9F07532438875" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Senaspis</taxonomicName>
Macquart, 1850: 437. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="5ACB19FEE3B834788889CFE852C6FB73" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis flaviceps" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviceps">Senaspis flaviceps</taxonomicName>
Macquart, 1850 (by monotypy).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3E5AA3991210508ABE1C932F40FCA66" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="6D3D87C71BAD59CF8963E27B9ACCBD1C" authority="Bezzi, 1912" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Protylocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protylocera" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Protylocera</taxonomicName>
Bezzi, 1912: 414 [unnecessary replacement name].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="367414E95833B9DEC131B1E04A3BC3CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="CA07C7C697672590E3E69B3F3FB10F7A" authority="Hull, 1949" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Triatylosus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triatylosus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Triatylosus</taxonomicName>
Hull, 1949: 398 (as subgenus). Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="BDDA10485C941056A7B8870684F8267D" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xylota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylota dibaphus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dibaphus">Xylota dibaphus</taxonomicName>
Walker, 1849 (by original designation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="397DD0F4D4BC1DF058F38C8D03A87048" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="generic diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C60BD686E71AB910631607DB8C49A675" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Generic diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4A5F6062C310189616E51D50815FEE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="552310D2E8960C52ED7646C5B76B2100" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0B82763EBB26A9322E0CF4ADFF76A3E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Senaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are morphologically characterized by the combination of the following characters: eyes bare and maculate (less conspicuous in dried specimens), dorsal facets in male usually only slightly larger than ventral facets, more pronounced so in 
<taxonomicName id="5B1785A922288E070717D38FEAAC666A" genus="S." lsidName="S. dibapha" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="dibapha">
<emphasis id="2A82A5226EA52E495AC677379F4CE4D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. dibapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Walker, 1849) and 
<taxonomicName id="FDF15018E193674691E189697A03B63F" genus="S." lsidName="S. nigrita" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="9B34F9DB51CB6B41DBA3B8E0832404F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bigot, 1859); antennal arista bare; frons in lateral view with distinct protuberance; wing with cell r1 usually closed and petiolate, or narrowly open at most (see Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2B03BDDD0FA8CC1A6E627AA7D35F4328" captionStart="Figures 68–73" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figures 68 - 73. Senaspis species, right wing 68 S. elliotii Austen (♂) 69 - 71 S. elliotii Austen close-up apical end 72 S. flaviceps Macquart (♂) 73 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures68-73" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486717" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">69</figureCitation>
) (if distinctly open then hyaline, without dark markings; see 
<taxonomicName id="3C0F572116EF25CEBAB48E880C626443" baseAuthorityName="Herve-Bazin" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis pennata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennata">
<emphasis id="437A24022F9291A191C4BF176C73CFD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Senaspis pennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="76067B65A6CF117D7EDA4D3FBB4920F5" captionStart="Figures 77–79" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figures 77 - 79. Senaspis species, right wing 77 S. umbrifera (Walker) (♂ holotype) 78 S. xanthorrhoea (Bezzi) (♂) 79 S. pennata (Herve-Bazin) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures77-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486719" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">79</figureCitation>
); vein R4+5 strongly sinuate; thorax with triangular (dorsomedial) part of anepimeron bare, katepimeron bare or pilose at least in dorsal part; metatibia with conspicuous pile on at least apical half ventrally (except in 
<taxonomicName id="C0ED20B20FC627BBE64C27009CF2E4AB" genus="S." lsidName="S. flaviceps" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="flaviceps">
<emphasis id="35B1126EA43B735D2CBAD80F7D8C74A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. flaviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
